    "Bitcoin has traditionally been viewed as the most established and widely recognized CC.",
    "In contrast, Ethereum has gained prominence because of its smart contract capabilities and decentralized applications (dApps) development.",
    "Second, Bitcoin and Ethereum have the highest trading volumes and liquidity levels compared to smaller CCs.",
    "This makes buying and selling CCs easier without significantly affecting the market prices.",
    "Higher liquidity attracts more institutional and retail investors."
